Generally, soil carbon pool is extremely in dynamic equilibrium with its ecosystem because, at one end, it acts as energy source for all microbial population and faunal community in soil environment, and on the other hand, due to having low density, it is preferentially removed by erosional process. The magnitude of change in SOC pool depends on the balance between carbon input (Eq. 1) and output  (Eq. 2).1CarbonInputCI=AGB+BGB+LB+AM\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
